subSubSection.paragraph:
Remarks.
Although this new species is similar in head shape and coloration to the Indian species 

D. ochraceus
Cameron

(Female, 
1
syntype
examined, 

BMNH

), it can easily be distinguished by the following combination of characters: 
1
) distinctly dilated tempora; 
2
) lack of elevation on head; 
3
) smaller eyes; 
4
) widely separated gular sutures; 
5
) elongate mandibles; 
6
) fully membranous aedeagus.
